  "title": "Understanding Arrays in Java",
  "lessonText": "Arrays are fundamental data structures that store multiple values in a single variable.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- An array is a collection of elements of the same type.\n- Arrays are fixed in size once created.\n- They can be accessed using an index, starting from 0.\n- Use cases include storing lists of items, such as numbers or strings.\n- Arrays can be multidimensional, allowing for more complex data storage."
  }
}
